1.Create autoload and bundle files
	 mkdir ~/.vim/autoload ~/.vim/bundle

2.Get Pathogen
	curl -LSso ~/.vim/autoload/pathogen.vim https://tpo.pe/pathogen.vim

3.Add the following to your .vimrc file, if it does not exist, create .vimrc file in your home directory
	execute pathogen#infect()

4.Clone the git repos of the plugins inside the ~/.vim/bundle folder

5. Some useful plugins:
  5.1. NERDTree - Simple file explorer - :NERDTree
  5.2. MRU - Lists most recently used files - :MRU
  5.3. NERDCommenter - CommentEasily - <Leader> cc and <Leader> cu
  5.4. SnipMate - Perfect snippet tool.

OR

Try Vundle - Yet another one of the coolest plugin management tool.
